Implemented Vercel Web Analytics for the portfolio React project.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/analytics` package using npm
- Package version added to dependencies in package.json
- package-lock.json updated with new dependency tree

### 2. Analytics Component Integration
Modified: `/src/App.jsx`
- Added import: `import { Analytics } from '@vercel/analytics/react'`
- Added `<Analytics />` component at the root level (after ThemeProvider closing tag)
- Placement ensures analytics tracking across all routes while respecting the existing component structure

## Implementation Details

Following the official Vercel documentation (fetched from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart), I:
1. Identified this as a React + Vite project
2. Used the React-specific installation instructions (`@vercel/analytics/react`)
3. Added the Analytics component to the main App component, ensuring it's rendered on all pages
4. Preserved existing code structure and styling

## Verification

✅ Build successful: `npm run build` completed without errors
✅ Dependencies installed: package-lock.json properly updated
✅ No new linting errors introduced (existing linting issues were pre-existing)

## Next Steps

After deployment to Vercel:
1. Navigate to the Analytics tab in your Vercel dashboard
2. Click "Enable" to activate Web Analytics for your project
3. Verify analytics are working by checking the browser's Network tab for requests to `/<unique-path>/view`

The Analytics component will automatically start tracking page views once the project is deployed to Vercel.
